# Fix GitHub Security reports

## Findings

Ran the three relevant GitHub security APIs against `getsentry/sentry-release-registry`:

| Source | Open count |
| --- | --- |
| `/security-advisories` | **0** |
| `/dependabot/alerts` | **0** (Dependabot security updates are enabled, no open alerts) |
| `/code-scanning/alerts` | **2 open** (both CodeQL `actions/missing-workflow-permissions`, severity `warning` / security severity `medium`) |

There is nothing to do for security advisories or Dependabot. The actionable items are the two open CodeQL alerts:

| # | File | Job | Issue |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 7 | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `main` (lines 7-32) | Workflow has no `permissions:` block â€” `GITHUB_TOKEN` falls back to repo/org defaults. |
| 2 | `.github/workflows/validate-pipelines.yml` | `files-changed` (lines 13-27) | Job has no `permissions:` block. (The `validate` job in the same file already declares its own permissions and is not flagged.) |

CodeQL's recommendation is to add an explicit least-privilege `permissions:` block so the principle of least privilege is documented and survives org-default changes / copies to other repos.

The third workflow, `.github/workflows/deploy-visualization.yml`, already declares workflow-level `permissions:` and is not flagged.

## Required changes

### 1. `.github/workflows/lint.yml`

Add a workflow-level `permissions:` block. The job only checks out code, runs Python tests, and verifies symlinks â€” `contents: read` is sufficient.

```yaml
name: lint then test
on:
  push:
    branches: [master, test-me-*]
  pull_request:

permissions:
  contents: read

jobs:
  main:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    ...
```

### 2. `.github/workflows/validate-pipelines.yml`

Add a workflow-level default `permissions:` block scoped to `contents: read`. The `validate` job's existing `permissions:` block (`contents: read`, `id-token: write`) overrides it for that job and stays as-is. The `files-changed` job (which only does `actions/checkout` + `paths-filter`) inherits the workflow-level default.

```yaml
name: Validate Deployment Pipelines

on:
    pull_request:
    push:
        branches: [master, test-me-*]

permissions:
    contents: read

concurrency:
    ...
```

Per-job `permissions:` blocks override the workflow default, so the existing `validate` job permissions remain unchanged.

